OL,3,CHosepipe ban: What you need to know as
OL,4,Chot weather leads to restrictions
OL,6,FAccording to regulator Ofwat, a
OL,7,Fhosepipe ban (or a Temporary Use Ban
OL,8,Fto use its official name) is a
OL,9,Frestriction imposed by water companies
OL,10,Fto try and save supplies during
OL,11,Fperiods of high demand or low supply,
OL,12,Fgenerally when it has been very dry
OL,13,Fand hot for long periods.
OL,15,FHow is a hosepipe ban enforced?
OL,17,FIn the UK, water firms have the
OL,18,Fauthority to impose fines of up to
OL,19,F#1,000 on anyone who violates the ban
OL,20,Funder the Water Industry Act.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
